    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Overview</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Aquarium at August 32nd is a short walking simulator game inspired by the well-known horror simulator Exit 8. In this game, players explore a spooky aquarium filled with anomalies and must find a way to exit by identifying these differences. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The rule of Aquarium at August 32nd is simple: turn back if there is an anomaly, or go forward if there is none. The game is completed when the number of jellyfish in the tank reaches eight. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Play time: 15 to 60 minutes </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Video Distribution Guidelines</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Both individuals and corporations can distribute without permission. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Monetization is possible only when using the functions provided by the video distribution site. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >We will not be liable for any damages whatsoever resulting from the distribution of videos of this game. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The contents of these guidelines are subject to change without notice. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Controls</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>[VR Controller (Meta Quest 2)]</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can choose from two types of control methods. The default is type A.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Control Type A</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left thumbstick up/down: Move forward, backward</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left thumbstick left/right: Rotate the camera</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Right thumbstick left/right: Rotate the camera with a snap turn (45 degrees)</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Control Type B</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left thumbstick up/down: Move forward, backward</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left thumbstick left/right: Move left/right in parallel</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Right thumbstick left/right: Rotate the camera with a snap turn (45 degrees)</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Common</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A button or X button: Turn the tunnel effect on/off</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >B button or Y button: Switch control type</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left grip: Run</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Right grip: Run</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Left trigger: Not used</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Right trigger: Not used</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p>",
